  "riddle": "1. Seek the bustling hub of finance that stands at the heart of the Big Apple. When did this storied exchange first open its doors to the public?\n\n2. Delve deeper into the founding year you found in clue 1. What single digit emerges when you sum the digits of that year down to one?\n\n3. What dark chapter in economic history took a significant toll starting in the 1930s across the United States, and what years encapsulate this catastrophic period?\n\n4. As the financial storm swept Asia, what was the pivotal year you discovered in the title of the page chronicling that crisis?\n\n5. In the vibrant city that houses a pivotal stock exchange, what is the height of the ground you stand upon in meters?\n\n6. Discover a German city known for its financial prowess that begins with “F.” How many people reside in this urban center as indicated in its summary?\n\n7. Now, turn your gaze to this same city: how high does the land rise beneath it above sea level?\n\n8. How many institutions of higher learning exist near this financial metropolis, according to your search?\n\n9. Take the elevation you found in clue 7 and combine it with the count of universities from clue 8. What is the absolute difference between these two values?\n\n10. In the heart of the Windy City lies an esteemed institution founded in the late 19th century—when was it established?\n\n11. From the legal helm of the United States, how many different languages does this department recognize?\n\n12. What star rating do travelers give to the legal institution you've just explored?\n\n13. Consider the number from clue 11 and transcribe it into Roman numerals. Count how many characters it takes in this ancient number system.\n\n14. Now compute the following: take the total of the results from clues 2, 4, 10, and 12, add them to 8, and then apply the modulus operator with 10. What single digit do you arrive at from that calculation?",
